I am creating an online game, its name is ‚Äú$TITLE$‚Äù.

You are a native English speaker and have a great knowledge of SEO, online marketing and content writing. You also have great knowledge in $TALENTS$. I need you to be our co-author of this online game.

I want you to write content on the quiz and output them in the following JSON format, and I have put some notes after each row.

{
  "content": {
    "title": "$TITLE$",
    "keywords", "...", // some keywords related to the quiz, split by comma
    "social_share_content": "I've got the %RESULT%. Take this quiz to check your results!", // please rephrase the sentence to make it adapt the topic, do not change the "%RESULT%", which is reserved for programming.
    "description": "...", //A description of about 100 characters
    "tips":["",""] // An array with two paragraphs to introduce the quiz
  },
  "meta": {
    "hashtag":"aTwitterStyleHashtag" // find a good hashtag for this content
  }
}

I have these i18n content for my online game:

$CONTENT_TXT$


I want you to generate two block of codes based on it.

First, I want you to generate a js object that I can include in my PUG file's javascript section, like this template:

game_ui:{
  owner_name:`!{content.game_ui.owner_name}`,
  owner_dialog:`!{content.game_ui.owner_dialog}`,
}

Then, I want you to generate a JSON that I can use in the PUG compile, like this template:

{
  "content": {
    "game_ui": {
      "owner_name": "Bill Gates",
      "owner_dialog": "Try to spend all my money ASAP!"
    }
  }
}

Here is a javascript object. It contains the text that will be used in an online game/app:

$JSON_TXT$

I need you to create two sections of code, based on it. The first one, should be a JSON object that contains the keys and the values, but in my template:

{
  "content": {
    "game_ui": {
      "key": "vaue",
    }
  }
}

The second is the JavaScript object with keys:

{
   key:"!{content.game_ui.keyname}
}


Let me give you some context so that you can understand my needs better.

The JSON object will be used for a PUG template.

The JavaScript object will be used in my js code, so it will extract variables from the JSON object.

Please output the two code sections for me, do not echo or explain yourself.
